{"lemma":"حَبِيساتٌ","slug":"حَبِيساتٌ","root":"ح.ب.س","root_slug":"ح-ب-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-س","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6910"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"imprisoned, restrained, secluded, limited"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb حَبَسَ (ḥabasa)."},"ipa":["/ħa.biːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6910","headword_ar":"حَبِيسٌ","root":"Hbs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobuwsN","text_ar":"مَحْبُوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pass. part. n. of 1,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Confined; restricted; limited;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bequeathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given, unalienably,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the sake of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether an animal or land or a house; (Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobuwsN","text_ar":"مَحْبُوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHab~asN","text_ar":"مُحَبَّسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHobasN","text_ar":"مُحْبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubusN","text_ar":"حُبُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) and, by contraction,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubosN","text_ar":"حُبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiysN","text_ar":"حَبِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a sing. and as a pl.: (Msb:) it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is sometimes used in the place of the pass. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~asa","text_ar":"حَبَّسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) it is also particularly applied to a horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bequeathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given, unalienably, to be used in the cause of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * Mgh, K;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the warriors, to ride it in war against unbelievers and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHobasN","text_ar":"مُحْبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHobuwsN","text_ar":"مَحْبُوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubosN","text_ar":"حُبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubusN","text_ar":"حُبُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) to what is, or are,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bequeathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given, unalienably,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not to be sold nor inherited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of palm-trees, or vines, &c., (K,) as land, and anything that is a source of profit, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself to remain unalienable, and the profit arising therefrom to be employed in the cause of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"religion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) but the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubus","text_ar":"حُبُس"},{"kind":"text","text":"which Mohammad is related to have made common property were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the pagan Arabs bequeathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gave, unalienably, for"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, and this I regard as the true reading, rather than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min","text_ar":"مِن"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the reading in the Mgh and L,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAy^ib","text_ar":"سَوَايِب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHaAy^ir","text_ar":"بَحَايِر"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and such as was called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAmK","text_ar":"حَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, L, TA:) Hr, in the Ghareebeyn, gives the reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubos","text_ar":"حُبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, says IAth, if correct, is a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubus","text_ar":"حُبُس"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [From"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hubos","text_ar":"حُبْس"},{"kind":"text","text":", used as a subst., has been formed, app. in postclassical times, the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaAsN","text_ar":"اَحْبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see De Sacy's “ Chrest. Ar., ” sec. ed., vol. i. p. 189.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiysapN","text_ar":"حَبِيسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also, [used as a subst.,] signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is bequeathed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given, unalienably, in the way of beneficence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAy^isu","text_ar":"حَبَايِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","Mgh","Msb","TA","S","K","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}